text: Patrick Dogue (born 9 March 1992) is a German modern pentathlete who won the national title in 2013 and 2015. He qualified for the 2016 Summer Olympics by placing second at the 2016 World Cup; he finished sixth in the Olympics. His brother Marvin is also an international modern pentathlete. ==References== Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Modern pentathletes at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic modern pentathletes of Germany Category:German male modern pentathletes
